               <p>EDWARD KIRKLEY. I am a livery stable-keeper -These four glasses are mine; I can be quite positive of two of them, by some lace on the frame, which matches the lace on the chaise - I had lent my chaise to Mr. 
               <persName id="t18290115-254-person1935">Martin</persName>
             the day before, and they were on his premises, next to his chaises: they are worth 8l.</p>
